    "# Experiment 1 — n>100 Retrieval Robustness (n=300)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Status:** robustness / external-validity check. **Not** a new core contribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What this tests.** The frozen Phase 4–6 finding is a *ranking*: **BM25 > dense**, **hybrid best (MRR@10)**, and the **Recall@5 order hybrid > BM25 > dense**, measured on a 21,050-chunk corpus from 100 EDGAR + 100 earnings documents. This notebook re-runs the **same three retrievers** over the **same frozen 60-query golden set**, but against a **3× larger corpus** (300 + 300 documents). The question is narrow and honest: *does the ranking survive when the haystack triples?*\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why this is valid (the seeded-prefix property).** `loaders.py` samples via `ds.shuffle(seed=42).select(range(n))`. `shuffle` permutes the *whole* dataset deterministically from the seed; `select(range(n))` takes a prefix of that one permutation — so the first 100 documents are byte-identical whether you load 100 or 300. `doc_id` is the post-shuffle row index, chunking is per-document (`chunk_id = doc_id_chunk_NNN`), and the dense cache is keyed on the chunk-id set — so the original 60 gold chunks reproduce **identically** inside the n=300 build, and the golden set's SHA-256 re-asserts trivially.\n",
    "\n",
    "**The honesty caveat to keep in the write-up.** A 3× corpus means *more distractor and near-duplicate chunks competing*, so absolute Recall/MRR may **soften** slightly. The robustness claim is about the **ordering holding under more distractors**, not about absolute parity with n=100. Report it that way.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Guard rail.** The golden hash proves \"same queries, same gold *ids*\" but not that those ids still map to the *same text*. So before the (slow) embed, a **hard validity gate** rebuilds the n=300 corpus and asserts every original chunk reappears with byte-identical text. If it fails, the notebook stops *before* wasting ~2h embedding on a corrupt control.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Outputs (all NEW files, `n300_` prefix; nothing frozen is overwritten):**\n",
    "`data/processed/n300_chunks.parquet`, `notes/n300_per_query_metrics.parquet`, `notes/n300_retrieval_summary.json`, `reports/figures/n300_comparison.png`, and a fresh dense cache under `data/embeddings_n300/`."
   ]
  },
